<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1051,1293]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brandt" authorityYear="1835" box="[281,404,1051,1077]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[281,404,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Holochilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises six recognized living species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Desmarest 1819)" baseAuthorityName="Desmarest" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[890,1273,1051,1077]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis box="[890,1056,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. brasiliensis</emphasis>
(Desmarest 1819)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thomas 1906)" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1906" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chacarius">
<emphasis box="[1288,1436,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. chacarius</emphasis>
(Thomas 1906)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pardinas, Teta, Voglino &amp; Fernandez 2013)" baseAuthorityName="Pardinas, Teta, Voglino &amp; Fernandez" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[335,959,1087,1113]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lagigliai">
<emphasis box="[335,463,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. lagigliai</emphasis>
(Pardiñas, Teta, Voglino &amp; Fernández 2013)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wagner 1842)" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[969,1270,1087,1113]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sciureus">
<emphasis box="[969,1094,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. sciureus</emphasis>
(Wagner 1842)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Allen 1904)" baseAuthorityName="Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1904" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="venezuelae">
<emphasis box="[1280,1436,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. venezuelae</emphasis>
(Allen 1904)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brants 1827)" baseAuthorityName="Brants" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[356,650,1123,1149]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Holochilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis box="[356,485,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. vulpinus</emphasis>
(Brants 1827)
</taxonomicName>
. The genus was distributed from central 
<collectingCountry box="[1103,1214,1123,1149]" name="Argentina" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1268,1366,1123,1149]" name="Uruguay" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
in the south to northern 
<collectingCountry box="[345,460,1159,1185]" name="Venezuela" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and the Guianas in the north and from the Amazonian regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[1178,1263,1159,1185]" name="Bolivia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1273,1327,1159,1185]" name="Peru" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1337,1432,1159,1185]" name="Ecuador" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[201,311,1195,1221]" name="Colombia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Colombia</collectingCountry>
to the Atlantic coast of eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[679,747,1195,1221]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Musser, G. G. &amp; Carleton, M. D." box="[763,1052,1194,1221]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="894 - 1531" refId="ref69694" refString="Musser, G. G. &amp; Carleton, M. D. (2005) Superfamily Muroidea. In: Wilson, D. &amp; Reeder, D. (Eds.), Mammal Species of the World: A Taxonomic and Geographic Reference, 3 rd ed. Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, Maryland, pp. 894 - 1531." type="book chapter" year="2005">Musser &amp; Carleton 2005</bibRefCitation>
; D’Elía 
<emphasis box="[1149,1200,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. 2015; 
<bibRefCitation author="Goncalves, P. R. &amp; Teta, P. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R." pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="325 - 335" refId="ref67704" refString="Goncalves, P. R., Teta, P. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. (2015) Genus Holochilus Brandt, 1835. In: Patton, J., Pardinas, U. F. J. &amp; D'Elia, G. (Eds.), Mammals of South America. 2. Rodents. University of Chicago Press, Chicago, Illinois, pp. 325 - 335." type="book chapter" year="2015">
Gonçalves 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). All cytogenetic data available for the genus was presented on 
<tableCitation box="[958,1042,1231,1257]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="20.[151,239,466,492]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="TABLE 4. Karyotype data of genus Holochilus. Species, diploid (2n) and fundamental (FN) numbers, collection localities, geographic coordinates and reference." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Table 4</tableCitation>
, and the distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens were presented on 
<figureCitation box="[888,956,1266,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1554,1578]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,641,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-232@18.[151,1436,633,1530]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Holochilus. (■) H. brasiliensis; (□) H. chacarius; (l) H. sciureus; (○) H. venezuelae; (▲) H. vulpinus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423627" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423627/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
